         <Observed_Examples>
            <Observed_Example>
               <Reference>CVE-2002-1532</Reference>
               <Description>HTTP GET without \r\n\r\n CRLF sequences causes product to wait indefinitely and prevents other users from accessing it.</Description>
               <Link>https://www.cve.org/CVERecord?id=CVE-2002-1532</Link>
            </Observed_Example>
            <Observed_Example>
               <Reference>CVE-2003-0195</Reference>
               <Description>Partial request is not timed out.</Description>
               <Link>https://www.cve.org/CVERecord?id=CVE-2003-0195</Link>
            </Observed_Example>
            <Observed_Example>
               <Reference>CVE-2005-2526</Reference>
               <Description>MFV. CPU exhaustion in printer via partial printing request then early termination of connection.</Description>
               <Link>https://www.cve.org/CVERecord?id=CVE-2005-2526</Link>
            </Observed_Example>
            <Observed_Example>
               <Reference>CVE-2002-1906</Reference>
               <Description>CPU consumption by sending incomplete HTTP requests and leaving the connections open.</Description>
               <Link>https://www.cve.org/CVERecord?id=CVE-2002-1906</Link>
            </Observed_Example>
         </Observed_Examples>
